news.title: HCC posts 45.7% decline in net profit to Rs 118.6 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Hindustan Construction Company's total income during October-December 2021 stood at Rs 2,695.89 crore, compared with Rs 2,416.93 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: DB Realty to raise Rs 1,575 crore through conversions of warrants
news.para: On February 3, the board of directors of DB Realty approved proposal to raise funds through issue of 12,70,00,000 warrants convertible into equivalent number of equity shares of the face value of Rs 10 each, it said in the regulatory filing.

news.title: Godrej Properties plans to invest Rs 400 crore to acquire about 10% stake in DB Realty
news.para: Godrej Properties and DB Realty will each contribute an additional 300 crore towards the equity platform focused on all slum rehabilitation and MHADA redevelopment projects in Mumbai.

news.title: China builders' cash squeeze drags down elevator-maker Kone
news.para: Kone, which relies on China for approximately 35% of its sales, gave a first estimate for its 2022 profits, expecting its adjusted operating income to be 1.18-1.33 billion euros ($1.33-$1.50 billion), slightly down from 1.31 billion in full-year 2021.

news.title: Brigade Enterprises posts Rs 46.41 crore net profit in Q3 FY22
news.para: Brigade Enterprises' net consolidated income stood at Rs 933.19 crore in Q3 FY22, a growth of 43% from Rs 653.65 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: NGT directs committee to submit report on plea about pollution by cement unit in Bihar
news.para: The NGT was hearing a plea filed by 'Chhawon Panchayat Vikas Samiti' alleging that functioning of a unit of N U Vista Cement Company (formerly known as Imami Cement Ltd) located at NN 2, 1644, Bheriyan Road, Kulhadiyan, in Kaimur is causing a health hazard to the nearby residents

news.title: BMC presents Rs 45,949 crore budget; no property tax for flats measuring up to 500 sq ft
news.para: In the budget, the Brihanmumbai Municipal Corporation announced 100 per cent relief from payment of property tax for the flats measuring up to 500 square feet of carpet area.

news.title: POPT raises funds at $2 million valuation from MRW Ventures & Riar Holdings
news.para: The companies have invested funds as foreign direct investment (FDI) in POPT. Seven other Indian angel investors also participated in the initial round of funding.

news.title: Households free to install rooftop solar panels by themselves, via vendors
news.para: "The Ministry of New and Renewable Energy has issued a simplified procedure for the residential consumers to get the rooftop solar plant installed by themselves or through any vendor of their choice under the Rooftop Solar Programme," a ministry statement said.

news.title: ARKADE Group acquires plot in Mumbai from Hercules Hoists for Rs 90 crore
news.para: Recently, ARKADE Group had announced the acquisition of six projects totaling 11,50,000 sq ft of construction area and has already invested Rs. 215 crore for this purpose.

news.title: CBI books Satya Constructions for Rs 11 crore loan fraud
news.para: The CBI booked the case against Satya Constructions Private Limited based on a complaint by SBI deputy general manager Ravi Mohan Saxena.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram corporation eyes private land at Bakery Junction for housing scheme
news.para: The project was launched in 2020; however the work could not be started as the beneficiaries have disagreed with the authorities regarding transit accommodation.

news.title: ZERUND raises pre-series A funding from NEDFi Venture Capital
news.para: ZERUND currently operates out of its manufacturing facility in Pathsala, Assam. It plans to utilize the part of the raised investment to set up a new facility that will have five times more capacity than the current one.

news.title: Indore civic body demolishes structures in illegal colonies
news.para: According to senior IMC officials, one Chetan Bhumiya was allegedly developing an illegal colony by the name of Lunia compound in around four acres of land situated on AB Road under Lasudia police station.

news.title: Skechers buys office space in Mumbai's Andheri for Rs 175 crore
news.para: The California-headquartered company has bought the office space spread across three floors of ready commercial tower Fulcrum in Andheri suburb of Mumbai from realty developer House of Hiranandani.
